  "doc_id": "45627",
  "text": "Step 3 is much smaller than for previous statements and can thus be disregarded. The retrieve of unique t in Step 1 can be performed in O(n) using a hash-based algorithm [CITATION_1] , where n is the size of the dataset, C. The indexing can be done in time O(p log p) where p is the number of periods, and since p << n this cost can be disregarded. The major cost in Step 1 is the 8-way join, and since p << n this cost will be dominated by the cost of the join of 4 copies of C, and even this can be performed in time O(n) using hash-joins [CITATION_2] . Since the number of source measures are a small constant, Step 2 can also be done in O(n) using hash-aggregation [CITATION_3] . In summary, the whole algorithm can be done in time O(n), where n is the size of C, and the algorithm thus scales linearly.",
